be more surprised?

00:30.613 --> 00:32.699
Guess who just sold
his bitching Camaro?

00:32.699 --> 00:35.868
The profit is currently
preventing you

00:35.868 --> 00:38.955
from seeing my hot bod.

00:39.622 --> 00:40.957
Why did you sell
that car?

00:40.957 --> 00:41.624
I thought you loved it.

00:41.624 --> 00:44.127
The guy who bought it
loved it more.

00:44.127 --> 00:45.587
So how much did we make?

00:45.587 --> 00:48.381
Start plucking and find out.

00:49.216 --> 00:54.429
The dollar values increase
as you approach the target area.

00:56.139 --> 00:56.681
[EXHALES]

00:56.681 --> 01:00.518
I-I'm gonna let you
approach your own target area.

01:02.062 --> 01:05.982
That's a far
too familiar trip.

01:06.441 --> 01:08.526
Anyway, we're up
about 2000.

01:08.526 --> 01:11.154
Well done. So what are we
going to do with it?

01:11.154 --> 01:15.283
You know,
besides, uh, shave it.

01:15.283 --> 01:17.744
Well, we're gonna put it
in the retirement fund.

01:17.744 --> 01:21.539
We're this much closer
to dying with a nice boat.

01:21.873 --> 01:25.543
So now let's do something
that may not be legal.

01:25.543 --> 01:28.421
But it's definitely tender.

01:29.381 --> 01:31.216
[PHONE RINGS]

01:31.883 --> 01:33.718
Oh! Hey, Dad.

01:33.718 --> 01:37.680
Great, I'll just stand here
like this.

01:37.680 --> 01:39.391
Oh, good, do you like it?

01:39.391 --> 01:41.893
He's thanking us for
the new laptop we sent them.

01:41.893 --> 01:45.188
Oh, by the way,
we sent them a new laptop.

01:45.188 --> 01:45.980
Yeah, what?

01:45.980 --> 01:49.651
Well, it doesn't matter
how much it cost. Dad--

01:49.651 --> 01:52.320
Dad, please don't
return it.

01:52.320 --> 01:55.907
Okay. Well, y-you can
do whatever you want.

01:55.907 --> 01:58.493
All right, bye-bye.

01:58.493 --> 02:02.789
God, it was a gift, it's not
his business how much it cost.

02:02.789 --> 02:05.041
How much did it cost?

02:05.208 --> 02:07.794
[SIGHS]
You know, he has worked
hard his whole life.

02:07.794 --> 02:09.504
Can't they ever
just enjoy their money?

02:09.504 --> 02:12.799
My mom can't use a tea bag
without wrapping it in foil

02:12.799 --> 02:16.052
and using it
three more times.

02:16.052 --> 02:18.846
Does that work?

02:20.056 --> 02:21.516
I mean, save some, sure.

02:21.516 --> 02:23.726
But, God, you gotta
enjoy your life.

02:23.726 --> 02:26.062
Uh, it's just their
Midwestern way of thinking.

02:26.062 --> 02:28.315
There's nothing wrong
with appreciating

02:28.315 --> 02:30.275
the value of a dollar.

02:30.275 --> 02:34.654
Speaking of appreciating
a dollar.

02:35.405 --> 02:37.407
You know what?

02:37.532 --> 02:39.951
We're not gonna put
that money away for our future.

02:39.951 --> 02:42.287
Okay, look, this is just
a reaction to your dad.

02:42.287 --> 02:43.455
And it's not sensible.

02:43.455 --> 02:44.164
That's the point.

02:44.164 --> 02:46.123
Let's just not be
sensible for once.

02:46.123 --> 02:50.962
Let's spend it all on one
fabulous, luxurious night.

02:50.962 --> 02:51.838
Audrey, finance is my business.

02:51.838 --> 02:54.632
I warn my clients against
this kind of thing all the time.

02:54.632 --> 02:56.968
Against what?
Enjoying their money?

02:56.968 --> 03:00.137
No, against listening
to their wives.

03:00.805 --> 03:01.848
Come on.

03:01.848 --> 03:03.558
That's the house's money.

03:03.558 --> 03:08.896
And I'm pretty sure
the house does not want it back.

03:09.146 --> 03:10.315
I don't know.
No.

03:10.315 --> 03:11.899
Please, just do this.

03:11.899 --> 03:14.361
Just don't be
like my father.

03:14.361 --> 03:16.696
All right, I won't be
like your father.

03:16.696 --> 03:17.655
But that doesn't preclude me

03:17.655 --> 03:20.950
