of my breast exam.

05:01.468 --> 05:05.555
Congratulations on marrying
an eighth grader.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.349
By the way, Audrey,
on the doctor's form

05:07.349 --> 05:10.226
I put you down as my "in case
of emergency" person.

05:10.226 --> 05:11.227
Oh. No problem.

05:11.227 --> 05:12.729
Why would you do that?

05:12.729 --> 05:14.314
In case there's
an emergency.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.524
It's pretty
self-explanatory.

05:17.066 --> 05:18.150
But I'm gonna
be your husband.

05:18.150 --> 05:20.320
I should be your
"in case of emergency" guy.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.529
Adam, I love you and there are

05:21.529 --> 05:22.822
so many things you are great at.

05:22.822 --> 05:24.616
But being responsible
with your cell phone

05:24.616 --> 05:26.576
is not one of those things.
Okay. You know what?

05:26.576 --> 05:29.203
Starting right now,
I'm gonna have my phone on me

05:29.203 --> 05:31.080
and turned on at all times.

05:31.080 --> 05:32.332
In fact...

05:32.332 --> 05:33.875
